channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: FashionSAP: Symbols and Attributes Prompt for Fine-grained Fashion Vision-Language Pre-training
item.description: We propose a method for fine-grained fashion vision-language pre-training based on fashion Symbols and Attributes Prompt (FashionSAP) to model fine-grained multi-modalities fashion attributes and characteristics.

item.title: Survey on Leveraging Uncertainty Estimation Towards Trustworthy Deep Neural Networks: The Case of Reject Option and Post-training Processing
item.description: In this paper, we present a systematic review of the prediction with the reject option in the context of various neural networks.

item.title: OccFormer: Dual-path Transformer for Vision-based 3D Semantic Occupancy Prediction
item.description: The vision-based perception for autonomous driving has undergone a transformation from the bird-eye-view (BEV) representations to the 3D semantic occupancy.

item.title: Another Vertical View: A Hierarchical Network for Heterogeneous Trajectory Prediction via Spectrums
item.description: In this paper, we bring a new ``view'' for trajectory prediction to model and forecast trajectories hierarchically according to different frequency portions from the spectral domain to learn to forecast trajectories by considering their frequency responses.

item.title: Topology Reasoning for Driving Scenes
item.description: Understanding the road genome is essential to realize autonomous driving.

item.title: Pointless Global Bundle Adjustment With Relative Motions Hessians
item.description: Bundle adjustment (BA) is the standard way to optimise camera poses and to produce sparse representations of a scene.

item.title: Fracture Detection in Pediatric Wrist Trauma X-ray Images Using YOLOv8 Algorithm
item.description: In this paper, YOLOv8 algorithm is used to train models on the GRAZPEDWRI-DX dataset, which includes X-ray images from 6, 091 pediatric patients with wrist trauma.

item.title: NeAT: Neural Artistic Tracing for Beautiful Style Transfer
item.description: As a component of curating this data, we present a novel model able to classify if an image is stylistic.

item.title: The Capacity and Robustness Trade-off: Revisiting the Channel Independent Strategy for Multivariate Time Series Forecasting
item.description: Our results conclude that the CD approach has higher capacity but often lacks robustness to accurately predict distributionally drifted time series.

item.title: The No Free Lunch Theorem, Kolmogorov Complexity, and the Role of Inductive Biases in Machine Learning
item.description: No free lunch theorems for supervised learning state that no learner can solve all problems or that all learners achieve exactly the same accuracy on average over a uniform distribution on learning problems.

item.title: PP-MobileSeg: Explore the Fast and Accurate Semantic Segmentation Model on Mobile Devices
item.description: To address this issue, we propose PP-MobileSeg, a semantic segmentation model that achieves state-of-the-art performance on mobile devices.

item.title: Pinpointing Why Object Recognition Performance Degrades Across Income Levels and Geographies
item.description: As an example, we show that mitigating a model's vulnerability to texture can improve performance on the lower income level.

item.title: Pixel-wise Guidance for Utilizing Auxiliary Features in Monte Carlo Denoising
item.description: Then we design our ensembling network to obtain per-pixel ensembling weight maps, which represent pixel-wise guidance for which auxiliary feature should be dominant at reconstructing each individual pixel and use them to ensemble the two denoised results of our denosiers.

item.title: Bayesian Optimization of Catalysts With In-context Learning
item.description: We show a prompting system that enables regression with uncertainty for in-context learning with frozen LLM (GPT-3, GPT-3. 5, and GPT-4) models, allowing predictions without features or architecture tuning.

item.title: Improving Neural Radiance Fields with Depth-aware Optimization for Novel View Synthesis

item.title: Efficient Feature Description for Small Body Relative Navigation using Binary Convolutional Neural Networks
item.description: We train and test our models on real images of small bodies from legacy and ongoing missions and demonstrate increased performance relative to traditional handcrafted methods.

item.title: Towards preserving word order importance through Forced Invalidation
item.description: Large pre-trained language models such as BERT have been widely used as a framework for natural language understanding (NLU) tasks.

item.title: Model sparsification can simplify machine unlearning
item.description: While exact unlearning is possible by conducting a model retraining with the remaining data from scratch, its computational cost has led to the development of approximate but efficient unlearning schemes.

item.title: Cooperative Coevolution for Non-Separable Large-Scale Black-Box Optimization: Convergence Analyses and Distributed Accelerations
item.description: Given the ubiquity of non-separable optimization problems in real worlds, in this paper we analyze and extend the large-scale version of the well-known cooperative coevolution (CC), a divide-and-conquer optimization framework, on non-separable functions.

item.title: Diffusion Recommender Model
item.description: In light of the impressive advantages of Diffusion Models (DMs) over traditional generative models in image synthesis, we propose a novel Diffusion Recommender Model (named DiffRec) to learn the generative process in a denoising manner.

item.title: Equivariant Graph Neural Networks for Charged Particle Tracking
item.description: Graph neural networks (GNNs) have gained traction in high-energy physics (HEP) for their potential to improve accuracy and scalability.

item.title: Towards Efficient Fine-tuning of Pre-trained Code Models: An Experimental Study and Beyond
item.description: Our experimental study shows that (1) lexical, syntactic and structural properties of source code are encoded in the lower, intermediate, and higher layers, respectively, while the semantic property spans across the entire model.

item.title: Automaton-Guided Curriculum Generation for Reinforcement Learning Agents
item.description: Experiments in gridworld and physics-based simulated robotics domains show that the curricula produced by AGCL achieve improved time-to-threshold performance on a complex sequential decision-making problem relative to state-of-the-art curriculum learning (e. g, teacher-student, self-play) and automaton-guided reinforcement learning baselines (e. g, Q-Learning for Reward Machines).

item.title: TodyNet: Temporal Dynamic Graph Neural Network for Multivariate Time Series Classification
item.description: Unfortunately, the existing deep learning-based methods neglect the hidden dependencies in different dimensions and also rarely consider the unique dynamic features of time series, which lack sufficient feature extraction capability to obtain satisfactory classification accuracy.

item.title: Task Difficulty Aware Parameter Allocation & Regularization for Lifelong Learning
item.description: In this paper, we propose the Parameter Allocation & Regularization (PAR), which adaptively select an appropriate strategy for each task from parameter allocation and regularization based on its learning difficulty.

item.title: Did we personalize? Assessing personalization by an online reinforcement learning algorithm using resampling
item.description: We use a working definition of personalization and introduce a resampling-based methodology for investigating whether the personalization exhibited by the RL algorithm is an artifact of the RL algorithm stochasticity.

item.title: RRHF: Rank Responses to Align Language Models with Human Feedback without tears
item.description: Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF) facilitates the alignment of large language models with human preferences, significantly enhancing the quality of interactions between humans and these models.

item.title: Prompt Learning for News Recommendation
item.description: Some recent \textit{news recommendation} (NR) methods introduce a Pre-trained Language Model (PLM) to encode news representation by following the vanilla pre-train and fine-tune paradigm with carefully-designed recommendation-specific neural networks and objective functions.

item.title: Evaluation of Differentially Constrained Motion Models for Graph-Based Trajectory Prediction
item.description: This research investigates the performance of various motion models in combination with numerical solvers for the prediction task.

item.title: CGXplain: Rule-Based Deep Neural Network Explanations Using Dual Linear Programs
item.description: Rule-based surrogate models are an effective and interpretable way to approximate a Deep Neural Network's (DNN) decision boundaries, allowing humans to easily understand deep learning models.

item.title: Curriculum-Based Imitation of Versatile Skills

item.title: Is ChatGPT a Good Sentiment Analyzer? A Preliminary Study
item.description: Recently, ChatGPT has drawn great attention from both the research community and the public.

item.title: Revisiting Test Time Adaptation under Online Evaluation

item.title: EVKG: An Interlinked and Interoperable Electric Vehicle Knowledge Graph for Smart Transportation System

item.title: GraphMAE2: A Decoding-Enhanced Masked Self-Supervised Graph Learner
item.description: Graph self-supervised learning (SSL), including contrastive and generative approaches, offers great potential to address the fundamental challenge of label scarcity in real-world graph data.

item.title: A Novel Point-based Algorithm for Multi-agent Control Using the Common Information Approach
item.description: The Common Information (CI) approach provides a systematic way to transform a multi-agent stochastic control problem to a single-agent partially observed Markov decision problem (POMDP) called the coordinator's POMDP.

item.title: Attention at SemEval-2023 Task 10: Explainable Detection of Online Sexism (EDOS)
item.description: In this paper, we have worked on interpretability, trust, and understanding of the decisions made by models in the form of classification tasks.

item.title: Neural Network Predicts Ion Concentration Profiles under Nanoconfinement
item.description: Overall, our deep learning model is a fast, flexible, and accurate surrogate model to predict ion concentration profiles in nanoconfinement.

item.title: Monte Carlo Linear Clustering with Single-Point Supervision is Enough for Infrared Small Target Detection
item.description: The core idea of this work is to recover the per-pixel mask of each target from the given single point label by using clustering approaches, which looks simple but is indeed challenging since targets are always insalient and accompanied with background clutters.

item.title: H2RBox-v2: Boosting HBox-supervised Oriented Object Detection via Symmetric Learning
item.description: With the increasing demand for oriented object detection e. g. in autonomous driving and remote sensing, the oriented annotation has become a labor-intensive work.

item.title: Three Recipes for Better 3D Pseudo-GTs of 3D Human Mesh Estimation in the Wild

item.title: WebBrain: Learning to Generate Factually Correct Articles for Queries by Grounding on Large Web Corpus
item.description: In this paper, we introduce a new NLP task -- generating short factual articles with references for queries by mining supporting evidence from the Web.

item.title: Deep Image Matting: A Comprehensive Survey
item.description: Image matting refers to extracting precise alpha matte from natural images, and it plays a critical role in various downstream applications, such as image editing.

item.title: Simulated Annealing in Early Layers Leads to Better Generalization
item.description: Our principal innovation in this work is to use Simulated annealing in EArly Layers (SEAL) of the network in place of re-initialization of later layers.

item.title: Reinforcement Learning from Passive Data via Latent Intentions
item.description: Passive observational data, such as human videos, is abundant and rich in information, yet remains largely untapped by current RL methods.
